snippet.textDisplay: The way these Ladz have blown up, you have to admit you do see similarities with NWA. The big question now is how will they progress as a group with half the team behind bars? Do they push on with just Spenny and J-Emz (holding the fort), introduce new members to the music scene or do they go the 'solo feature' route with other artists on home-soil and overseas? Hopefully we don't see them end up like Deathrow Records, who had a a great run of hits but were only around for a few years. The music up until now has been unreal and I'm hoping they beat the odds that are being stacked against them at this time.
